pocketbook – by trading in their old car for a new hybrid.  But, they were
concerned about taking on car payments in addition to their mortgage, so we
agreed to meet to explore their options.</span></p>

<p class=MsoBodyText2><span lang=EN style='font-family:Verdana;font-style:normal'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoBodyText2><span lang=EN style='font-family:Verdana;font-style:normal'>        Michelle
and Aaron thought their only choice was to refinance their mortgage, lower
their monthly payment, and use the money they saved to make car payments. 
Since they had a fixed-rate mortgage with a great interest rate, as an
alternative I suggested a home equity line of credit to pay for the entire cost
of the new car, at a much lower interest rate than a traditional car loan. 
They were delighted with that suggestion, since they could go green – and save
some green, as well!</span></p>

